Press Releases.Title: 465 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 16 May 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 465 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore, the vast majority of whom are Work Permit holders residing in foreign worker dormitories. Four cases are Singaporeans/ Permanent Residents. 

2.     We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 

MINISTRY OF HEALTH
16 MAY 2020
